IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: Women's Funding Alliance advances leadership and economic opportunity for women and girls in Washington State. The organization shines a spotlight on pressing issues and brings solutions to philanthropy, community organizations, business and government.
IRS990.MissionDesc: Women's Funding Alliance advances leadership and economic opportunity for women and girls in Washington State.
IRS990.Desc: Economic Opportunity: Women's Funding Alliance increases women's financial stability and narrows wage gaps. Our programs include the Thrive Initiative, which improves educational and economic opportunity for single mothers. Our programs also include the 100% Talent Initiative, which engages employers to narrow the gender wage gap and increase equity in the workplace.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: Leadership: Women's Funding Alliance expands women's leadership - as they develop and serve as community leaders and elected and appointed officials. Our programs include the LEAD Initiative, which increases women's voice and parcitipation in civic leadership. The GLOW Initiative builds the capacity of girl-serving organizations to increase girls' participation.

Part XII, Line 2d: Other expenses and losses per audited F/S
Grantmaker's Description of How Grants are Used
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: We require grantees to submit a letter of intent and full proposal that is vetted by staff and volunteers. Grantees conduct and share with WFA reports of all activities and outcomes as compared to those outlined in the proposal.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11b: Form 990 Review Process
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Management and Board Officers and Directors review the Form 990 after it is prepared as a component of the Board packet, and before it is submitted to the IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Staff and Board Officers and Directors review and sign the policy on an annual basis. They are all covered under the policy. Determinations of a conflict are made at the Board level.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15a: Compensation Review & Approval Process - CEO, Top Management
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Executive Committee of the Board reviews President & CEO salary levels for similar organizations, taking into account organization type, size of budget, number of staff, etc. to arrive at a salary that is fair, equitable, and market-based. In addition, they take into account the current President & CEO's tenure and track record of accomplishments as they set the salary level.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 19: Other Organization Documents Publicly Available
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: These documents are available upon request.
